about me

I'm a highly collaborative and supportive team player that enjoys coming together on every project to ensure the clients get the very best result.

My Mission

Build the best product that creates the most value for my employer, and support my team in any way necessary.

My Values

I strive to go above and beyond for my employer no matter the challenge. I aim to deliver my very best work every single day.

item.title: Projects
item.dc:creator: spnardone2
item.content:encoded:
My Projects

Web Design

One of my favorite things to do is to develop websites. This site you are looking at right now has gone through hundreds of revisions to reach the point it is currently at. This is nothing like when I created it for my web dev class years ago.

There are others I have done in the past for family and friends however I have since lost the code for them and am currently rebuilding my web dev repository.

Click below to see my GitHub!

Check it out

Cyber Security

Cyber security is an area in which I feel I could really make a difference in the world. I enjoy learning about a lot of different things and how they all work together.

Click below to see my GitHub!

Check it out

Programming

I enjoy programming because most of my life I have worked with materials and tools to build/repair/remodel things and places. Programming is very similar in that you learn how to work with a set of tools like loops and conditionals which can be used with every material or language. From there your only real limitation is you.

Click below to see my GitHub!

Check it out

Stephen P. Nardone II

Areas of Interest

Web Development

Since learning web development it has become something of a hobby of mine. I enojy the creativity it brings out in me.

Cyber Security

Cyber Security is my main focus and what I would like to build a career doing. I excel at reverse engineering but enjoy all aspects of cyber security.

Programming

Programming has become a bit of a passion of mine. I have always worked in fields where you use materials and tools to solve problems and well that is exactly what programming does just digitally.

About Me

I spent most of my adult life working on houses and vehicles. Everything from small tasks like oil changes and touch-up painting to larger jobs like engine rebuilds and whole home remodels. Little did I know, these project management and problem-solving skills I was building would come in handy in my newfound career path.

Find Out More

QUESTIONS?

Whether you're curious about my availability, or employment status, or have a business proposal, I'm here to answer any questions and will respond in a timely manner.

Let's Talk Now!
